Our political party is little without its members, those who tirelessly work to keep our party-movement alive in song and action. However due to daily stresses and competition from the capitalist entertainment sector, only a small amount of our membership is active at any given point. By allocating more money to the budgets of local chapters, we may be able to do something to improve the situation.

[? if sa_strength > 500 : However, it feels frivolous to spend on sports and choirs when the fascists are murdering us in the streets. ?]

